column5: Null cipher suites do not provide any data encryption and data integrity.
The SSL/TLS server accept encryption chich doesn't require authentication of the server.
The TLS/SSL server supports export cipher suites intentionally crippled to conform to US export laws. Symmetric ciphers used in export cipher suites typically do not exceed 56 bits.
Really weak cipher algorithms are accepted by the server https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Old_backward_compatibility
Cipher key used for some cipher algorithms are too small (<128 bits).
Weak cipher algorithms are accepted by the server https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Intermediate_compatibility_.28default.29
